Version 2.11:
- [+] 19 Oct 2007, Alien - Improvement (0023634): The hardcoded table prefix was removed.
- [+] 28 Aug 2007, Alien - Improvement (0017863): The ability to specify separate SKU for each product options combination is added.
- [!] 18 Apr 2007, Sheriff - Bug (0019278): The "Automatically create product's inventory record" option conflicted with the "Clone inventory data when product is cloned" option. Fixed.

Version 2.10:
- [!] 15 Mar 2007, Sheriff - Bug (0017736): When the "Redirect customer to cart when adding a product" option was not selected and a customer looked at some category page, the "Product is out of stock!" notification message was not displayed to the customer. Fixed.
- [+] 20 Dec 2006, Sheriff - Improvement (0014510): Now product inventory can be enabled automatically for every new imported product.  Previously it could only be enabled for manually created products in the admin zone.

Version 2.9:
- [!] 20 Jul 2006, Osipov - Bug (0009390): Redundant functionality was available in templates. Fixed.

Version 2.8:
- [+] 17 Mar 2006, Sheriff - Improvement: Compatibility with the future versions (2.2+) of LiteCommerce software and PHP 5+ was added.
- [!] 23 Jan 2006, Sheriff - Bug (0005632): A few typos were fixed.
- [!] 20 Sep 2005, Sheriff - Bug (0004532): Problem importing product options containing singly quote symbol. Fixed.

Version 2.7:
- [+] 12 Sep 2005, Sheriff - Improvement (0004114): For products with stock quantities below zero, "Out of stock" sign now comes up on the customer front end.
- [!] 30 Aug 2005, Sheriff - Bug (0003898): The module didn't regard the "Disabled for sale" product settings. Fixed.

Version 2.6:
- [+] 02 Aug 2005, Sheriff - Improvement (0003677): All out-of-stock products, including the products with product options set, can now excluded from inventory.
- [!] 29 Jul 2005, Asd - Bug (0003668): When admin tried to add a new tracking option for the product option with the single quote in the class name, it caused a crash with an SQL error. Fixed.
- [!] 29 Jul 2005, Asd - Bug (0003634): The inventory records sometimes were not initialized correctly when "ProductOptions" module was enabled. Fixed.
- [+] 18 Jul 2005, Asd - Improvement (0003491): Now product inventory can be enabled automatically for every new product (new configuration option for module was added). Previously it could only be enabled on per product basis.

Version 2.5:
- [+] 21 Jun 2005, Asd - Improvement: Now product inventory can be created from scratch through CSV file. Previously it could only be updated.
- [!] 21 Jun 2005, Asd - Bug: With ProductOptions module installed and deactivated, product inventory export caused duplication of fields in CSV files. Fixed.
- [+] 21 Jun 2005, Asd - Improvement: A notification message has been added to inform a customer when the amount of a product that he attempts to add to his shopping cart exceeds the stock quantity.
- [+] 30 May 2005, Sheriff - Improvement: Templates were modified to make them compatible with the new version of the "ProductAdviser" module.

Version 2.4:
 - [!] 07 Mar 2005, Asd - Bug: The compiled code/templates cache was not cleaned up during the module uninstallation. Fixed.
 - [+] 04 Mar 2005, Asd, Sheriff - Improvement: The ability to clone inventory data of a product during the cloning of the product. Now admin can enable/disable this feature in the "Module InventoryTracking settings" dialogue - there is the option "Clone inventory data when product is cloned".
 - [!] 02 Mar 2005, Asd - Bug: When admin tried to add a new tracking option with the same parameters as an option that already existed, it caused a crash with an SQL error. Fixed. 
 - [+] 02 Mar 2005, Asd - Improvement: The ability to track products with defined product options without tracking the product options even if the ProductOptions add-on is installed was added.

Version 2.3:
 - [!] 22 Dec 2004, Sheriff - Bug: Under certain conditions the behavior of some functions was changed on PHP 4.3.10 with some Zend enhancements ('unset()' function, for example). Fixed (additional verification was added).

Version 2.2:
- [!] 09 Dec 2004, Sheriff - Bug: Inventory properties (amount) got lost sometimes in the process of product export. Fixed.
- [!] 24 Nov 2004, Sheriff - Bug: Obsolete product information (information about lost products) stored in the database caused incorrect product export. Fixed.

Version 2.1:

